    {
        "content": "<p>You can’t put an addition which gives you the same result as the usual addition over the reals indeed. What you should rather do I think is to prove that if a and b are not -1 then a+b+ab isn’t either, and then you can directly define your group operation.</p>",
        "id": 506590495,
        "sender_full_name": "Etienne Marion",
        "timestamp": 1742335970
    },
